<% content_for :title do %>PostcardMailer.us Help<% end %>

<p style="margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Hello <%= @email %>,</p>
<p style="margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Re: <%= @subject %></p>

<h2 style="color: #0066cc; margin-top: 1.5em;">WELCOME TO POSTCARDMAILER.US!</h2>

<p style="margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Thank you for requesting help with PostcardMailer.us. Below you'll find instructions for using our service through email commands.</p>

<h2 style="color: #0066cc; margin-top: 1.5em;">Available Commands</h2>

<div style="background-color: #f5f5f5; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px; margin-bottom: 20px;">
  <h3 style="margin-top: 0; color: #0066cc;">1. Sign Up</h3>
  <p style="margin: 0 0 1em 0;">To create a new account:</p>
  <ol style="margin-left: 20px;">
    <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Send an email to <strong style="color: #000;">signup@postcardmailer.us</strong></li>
    <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Include your <strong style="color: #000;">full name</strong> in the subject line</li>
    <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5em;">In the email body, include your complete mailing address (street, city, state, ZIP)</li>
  </ol>
  <p style="margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Example:<br>
    To: signup@postcardmailer.us<br>
    Subject: John Smith<br>
    Body: 123 Main Street<br>
    San Francisco, CA 94110
  </p>
</div>

<div style="background-color: #f5f5f5; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px; margin-bottom: 20px;">
  <h3 style="margin-top: 0; color: #0066cc;">2. Add an Address</h3>
  <p style="margin: 0 0 1em 0;">To add a new address to your account:</p>
  <ol style="margin-left: 20px;">
    <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Send an email to <strong style="color: #000;">adduser@postcardmailer.us</strong></li>
    <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Include a <strong style="color: #000;">nickname</strong> for this address in the subject line</li>
    <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5em;">In the email body, include the recipient's name and address</li>
  </ol>
  <p style="margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Example:<br>
    To: adduser@postcardmailer.us<br>
    Subject: mom<br>
    Body: Jane Smith<br>
    456 Oak Avenue<br>
    Chicago, IL 60601
  </p>
  <p style="margin: 0 0 1em 0;"><em style="color: #666;">Note: Our AI-powered address parser will automatically standardize and validate the address format to ensure accurate delivery through the US Postal Service.</em></p>
</div>

<div style="background-color: #f5f5f5; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px; margin-bottom: 20px;">
  <h3 style="margin-top: 0; color: #0066cc;">3. Send a Postcard</h3>
  <p style="margin: 0 0 1em 0;">To send a postcard to someone in your address book:</p>
  <ol style="margin-left: 20px;">
    <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Send an email to <strong style="color: #000;">$nickname@postcardmailer.us</strong></li>
    <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Use the subject line for the <strong style="color: #000;">message</strong> to the recipient</li>
    <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Attach the <strong style="color: #000;">image</strong> you want to use for the postcard</li>
  </ol>
  <p style="margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Example:<br>
    To: mom@postcardmailer.us<br>
    Subject: Had a great time in San Francisco!<br>
    Attachment: vacation-photo.jpg
  </p>
</div>

<div style="background-color: #f5f5f5; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px; margin-bottom: 20px;">
  <h3 style="margin-top: 0; color: #0066cc;">4. Get Help</h3>
  <p style="margin: 0 0 1em 0;">To receive these instructions again:</p>
  <ol style="margin-left: 20px;">
    <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Send an email to <strong style="color: #000;">help@postcardmailer.us</strong></li>
  </ol>
</div>

<h2 style="color: #0066cc; margin-top: 1.5em;">Important Notes</h2>
<ul style="margin-left: 20px;">
  <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5em;">New accounts require verification before you can send postcards</li>
  <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Make sure addresses are complete and formatted correctly</li>
  <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Image attachments should be clear and high resolution for best results</li>
  <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5em;">The subject line is used to identify the recipient by their nickname</li>
</ul>

<p style="margin: 0 0 1em 0;">If you have any other questions or need assistance, please reply to this email.</p> 